This page attempts to list all Dylan documentation sources.


.. contents:


Reference
=========

* `Dylan Reference Manual (DRM) </static/books/drm/>`_ (`Errata`_) - The
  official definition of the Dylan language and standard library.

* {{Libraries}} - Find docs for specific Dylan libraries.

.. _Errata: /static/books/drm/Errata


Tutorials
=========

* `Getting Started with Dylan`_ (`multi-page`__) - A quick tutorial by Eric
  Kidd

* {{Code Examples}} - Find examples of specific Dylan language constructs.

* `Dylan Programming`_ - This book takes you through an airport example.

* `A First Look at Dylan`_ - An article for MacTech by Steve Strassmann.  It
  covers classes, functions and modules, and provides good examples.

* `Converting Common Lisp to Dylan`_ - Some notes for Lisp hackers interested
  in Dylan.

__ /static/gdref/tutorial/
.. _Getting Started with Dylan: /static/gdref/tutorial.html
.. _Dylan Programming: /static/books/dpg/
.. _A First Look at Dylan: http://www.mactech.com/articles/develop/issue_21/21strassman.html
.. _Converting Common Lisp to Dylan: http://www.norvig.com/ltd/doc/ltd.html


Gwydion Dylan Docs
==================

* `Gwydion Dylan User's Manual`_ - Includes a brief tutorial on creating and
  compiling Dylan programs, plus a reference for the d2c compiler and other
  tools.
 
* `Updated Gwydion Dylan Library Reference`_

* `Gwydion Dylan Library Reference`_ (`multi-page`__)
 
* `Gwydion Dylan Maintainer's Manual`_ (`multi-page`__) - Reference describing
  tool internals.

* `d2c internals doc`_ (`multi-page`__)
 
.. _Gwydion Dylan User's Manual: /static/gdref/gduser.html
.. _Updated Gwydion Dylan Library Reference: /static/gdref/gdcore/html/index.html
.. _Gwydion Dylan Library Reference: /static/gdref/gdlibs.html
__ /static/gdref/gdlibs/gdlibs.html
.. _Gwydion Dylan Maintainer's Manual: /static/gdref/gdmaint.html
__  /static/gdref/gdmaint/
.. _d2c internals doc: /static/gdref/gdapi.html
__ /static/gdref/gdapi/


Open Dylan Docs
===============

These docs still refer to "Functional Developer", which was the name of Open
Dylan before it became open source.

* `Getting Started with Functional Developer`_ - Describes Open Dylan's
  interactive development environment

* `Common Dylan and Functional Extensions library reference`_ - Describes the
  common-dylan library and Open Dylan's language extensions.

* `System and I/O library reference`_ - Describes libraries for interacting
  with the host environment.

* `Building Applications Using DUIM`_ - User guide for the Dylan User Interface
  Manager, a portable GUI development toolkit.

* `DUIM library reference`_ - Complete DUIM library reference.

* `C FFI`_ - How to interface with C libraries via the C Foreign Function
  Interface.

* `Microsoft win32 API` - How to use the MS win32 API in Open Dylan.

* `OLE, COM, ActiveX and DBMS Reference`_

* `CORBA Reference`_

